Use the quotient rule for exponents: when dividing powers with the same base, subtract the exponent of the denominator from the exponent of the numerator.

a)  y^{43}/y^{37}=y^{43−37}=y^{6}

b)  10^{15}/10^{7}=10^{15−7}=10^{8}

So the simplified results are y⁶ and 10⁸.

Recall the quotient rule for exponents:

For any non-zero base a and integers m, n,
a^m / a^n = a^{m−n}.

a)  b^{19} / b^{11}  
   = b^{19−11}  
   = b^{8}.

b)  z^{5} / z^{11}  
   = z^{5−11}  
   = z^{−6}  
   = 1 / z^{6}.

